## Routing Flow Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User visits URL"] --> B{"Authenticated?"}
    B -- No --> C{"Is protected route?"}
    C -- Yes --> D["Redirect → /login"]
    C -- No --> E["Allow (landing, public, auth pages)"]
    B -- Yes --> F{"Path = '/' or auth page?"}
    F -- Yes --> G["Fetch profile role"]
    G --> H["Redirect → role dashboard"]
    F -- No --> I{"Is protected route?"}
    I -- No --> J["Allow (public pages like /services, /about)"]
    I -- Yes --> K["Fetch profile role"]
    K --> L{"Role matches route?"}
    L -- Yes --> M["Allow access"]
    L -- No --> N["Redirect → own dashboard"]
    K --> O{"Suspended/blocked?"}
    O -- Yes --> P["Sign out → /login"]
```

## Route Access Matrix (Final)

| Route Pattern | Guest | Customer | Partner | Admin |
|:---|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
| `/` (landing) | ✅ | → `/dashboard` | → `/partner/dashboard` | → `/admin/dashboard` |
| `/login`, `/register` | ✅ | → `/dashboard` | → `/partner/dashboard` | → `/admin/dashboard` |
| `/services` (public) | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| `/about`, `/help`, `/terms` | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| `/dashboard`, `/bookings` | → login | ✅ | → `/partner/dashboard` | → `/admin/dashboard` |
| `/services/[cat]/[id]` | → login | ✅ | → `/partner/dashboard` | → `/admin/dashboard` |
| `/partner/*` | → login | → `/dashboard` | ✅ | → `/admin/dashboard` |
| `/admin/*` | → login | → `/dashboard` | → `/partner/dashboard` | ✅ |

## Security Notes

- **Server-side enforcement**: All routing rules are enforced in the proxy (runs before page render) — cannot be bypassed by client-side navigation, browser back button, direct URLs, or new tabs
- **Defense-in-depth**: Landing page has an additional server-side redirect as a safety net
- **Role verification**: Always fetched from `profiles` DB table (never from `user_metadata` or client state)
- **Session handling**: Supabase SSR cookies with `HttpOnly` + `Secure` flags (managed by `@supabase/ssr`)
- **Suspended accounts**: Detected and signed out at proxy level before any page renders

